Shriveling Touch			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Ghost.Corrupter	PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Corrupting Touch,Agony Touch																													PRESTAT:1,CHA=13																													DESC:Choose one physical ability score (Strength, Dexterity or Constitution). When you touh a living creature or a ghost, you can cause permanent drain to that score				STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|FEAT|PC[Agony Touch]	SELECT:1																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.38													BENEFIT:You can make a touch attack that deals 1d4 points of permanent ability drain to the selected ability score of a living creature or ghost. When you are manifested fully or attacking incorporeal opponents you add our Strength modifier to attack rolls. When you are incorporeal, you add your Dexterity modifier to attack rolls. If the attack scores a critical hit, the draining is doubled (ghosts are not subject to critical hits). Only one kind of damage or effect from the path of the corrupter applies from each attack. You may use this attack once per day per character level. You do not have to use this ability when you touch another creature, and creatures that touch you are not subject to this ability drain
